.NH 3
Special RFBD Considerations on an SGI running 4Sight
.PP
If your SGI is running 4Sight (also known as MAX) rather than MEX,
and you desire to run the remote frame buffer daemon, so that remote
machines can display images on your workstation,
you will need to run these additional commands:
.sp .5
.nf
.ft B
	mkdir /usr/brlcad/etc/NeWS
	cp contributed/init.ps /usr/brlcad/etc/NeWS/init.ps
.ft R
.fi
.sp .5
This will allow
.B fbserv
to start the 4Sight window system when a remote connection is made.
