a1508 38
On an SGI 4-D, warning messages from the compiler of the form:
.sp .5
.nf
.ft B
uopt: Warning: main: parts of procedure have no exit point
.ft R
.fi
.sp .5
represent a warning from SGI's compiler that can safely be ignored;
it is intended to signal infinite loops, but sometimes cries "wolf".
.PP
Presently, it is not possible to open a graphics window unless a
user is logged in on the console.
This adversely affects the usefulness of the network frame buffer daemon
\fBrfbd\fR and remote shell invocations of \fBpl-sgi\fR.
The frame buffer library contains optional code to automatically start up the
window system (``4Sight'') if no user is logged in;  this uses the
ps_open_PostScript() subroutine to check the status of the window system.
Alas, through IRIX release 3.1C, 4Sight release 1.3, this routine is
not compatible with the ``shared'' versions of the graphics library.
Because the shared library results in smaller executable files,
the default configuration uses shared libraries, and requires that
you must be logged into the console of the workstation in order to
obtain a graphics display.
If you wish to have the automatic behavior, and don't mind the fact that
the executable files will not be sharable across different 4D models,
then modify the two \fB#if\ 1\fR statements in the 4D section of
\fBCakefile.defs\fR to be \fB#if\ 0\fR.
.PP
When the software is compiled using the ``shared'' libraries,
binaries are compatible across the entire 4-D hardware line,
from personal Iris through the GTX.  However, there is
one SGI graphics library subroutine that is not properly interfaced
to the shared library mechanism (ps_open_PostScript()).  Therefore,
if the \fBrfbd\fR(8) remote frame buffer daemon is to be used,
the binaries must be model-specific.  Otherwise, the binaries
can be generic for any 4-D.
.PP
a1541 12
Under C 3.0, which is /bin/cc on XMP UNICOS 4.0 and on Cray-2
UNICOS 4.0, the \fBlgt\fR program will not compile due to
a compiler bug:
.sp .5
.ft B
.nf
 * F * :../lgt/hmenu.c: 207: CC058 - Invalid Initialization
.fi
.ft R
Get your site analyst to request the necessary compiler fixes,
or get C 4.0 or ANSI C.
.PP
