.NH 2
DEC VAX, 4.1 BSD and DEC Ultrix
.PP
The C compiler on 4.1 BSD UNIX systems, and on DEC Ultrix systems
is unable to handle pointers to functions which return \fBvoid\fR.
In the section of \fBCakefile.defs\fR for the VAX, it is necessary
to uncomment this definition,
which maps all \fBvoid\fR objects to \fBint\fR objects, a harmless
workaround:
.sp .5
.nf
.ft B
	#	define	CC_DEFS	-Dvoid=int
.ft R
.fi
.sp .5
.NH 2
SGI 4-D, Software Version 3.0
.PP
When the software is compiled using the ``shared'' libraries,
binaries are compatible across the entire 4-D hardware line,
from personal Iris through the GTX.  However, there is
one SGI graphics library subroutine that is not properly interfaced
to the shared library mechanism (ps_open_PostScript()).  Therefore,
if the \fBrfbd\fR(8) remote frame buffer daemon is to be used,
the binaries must be model-specific.  Otherwise, the binaries
can be generic for any 4-D.  See the comments in \fBCakefile.defs\fR
and libfb/if_4d.c for more details.
.PP
There is utterly no support for SGI 4-D machines running SGI software
releases earlier than 3.0 \(em they don't work well.
