SGI 4-D/GT, Version 3.0
d1360 9
a1368 22
Silicon Graphics Iris 4-D systems with the ``Graphics Turbo'' (GT)
hardware require a completely different set of vendor-specific
support code for the framebuffer library,
due to the significant changes in the underlying hardware.
In addition, there is support for multi-processors.
In \fBCakefile.defs\fR,
the shell script \fBsetup.sh\fR should correctly
select from configuration 1, 2, or 3, and
update the definition for SGI_TYPE.
For example:
.sp .5
.nf
.ft B
#	define	SGI_TYPE	3
.ft R
.fi
.sp .5
would be set if you were on a 4-D non-GT running SGI software Release 2.
The three choices are:
1)  [4gt] 4D-GT hw on SGI sw Release 3.1,
2)  [4d] non-GT hw on SGI sw Release 3.1, and
3)  [4d] non-GT hw on SGI sw Release 2.
d1370 2
a1371 2
You may wish to verify that \fBsetup.sh\fR make the correct selection.
Note that selection #2 has not been tested at BRL.
